    "status": "present",
    "items": [
      "Definition 2 A relation R in a set A is called universal relation , if each element of A is related to every element of A, i.e., R = A \u00d7 A.",
      "Both the empty relation and the universal relation are some times called trivial relations .",
      "Definition 3",
      "Definition 4"
